The curriculum consist of lectures and e-lectures, ineractive practical courses and seminars, independent homework. Course covers basic principles and concepts of pharmaceutical biotechnology, its application in drug development, and use in medicine and pharmacotherapy. Provides insight into the analytical methods in pharmaceutical biotechnology.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To learn the basic concepts of biotechnology and pharmaceutical biotechnology and its application in medicine and pharmacotherapy.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1.	Has aquired basic knowledge in biotechnology and pharmaceutical biotechnology 2.	Has gained an understanding on the application and perspectives of pharmaceutical biotechnology in drug          development and pharmacotherapy 3.	Understands basical laboratory methods in pharmaceutical biotechnology 4.	Improved skills in critical reading and analysis of scientific literature of the field  5.	Improved skills on preparation and presentation of scientific information of the field
